  <p class="article-kicker">About</p>
  <h1 class="article-title">Whatever's being said, wherever it's coming from.</h1>

  <div class="article-body">
    <p>RumorMouth is an entertainment site built on one simple rule: if we didn't report it ourselves, we tell you exactly where it came from.</p>

    <p>Three kinds of content run here, and we treat them differently on purpose.</p>

    <p><strong>The Wire</strong> is a curated feed pulled from outside newsrooms — Variety, TMZ, E! News, Us Weekly, Rolling Stone, and others. For every one of these, you'll see a short excerpt and a clear link back to where the story was actually reported. We never republish someone else's reporting in full and pass it off as our own — the point of the Wire is to help you find good coverage, not replace it.</p>

    <p><strong>Press releases</strong> are republished in full, but only from wire services like PR Newswire that specifically license their content for that purpose. Anything in this section is here because the source explicitly wants it distributed.</p>

    <p><strong>Hot Takes</strong> are original — written by the RumorMouth desk, not aggregated from anywhere. This is where we actually put our own voice on the page.</p>

    <p>RumorMouth runs on an automated pipeline for the Wire and Release sections, refreshed regularly throughout the day, alongside original writing added by hand. If something looks wrong — a broken link, a source that shouldn't be there, a factual error in one of our own pieces — we want to hear about it. See <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>.</p>
  </div>

